# Constitution (always)
This is an AI-powered **Event Intelligence Platform**. Events are the primary entity; sources are folded into events. It is NOT a social network, news site, or blog.

Guiding order: architecture > speed; simplicity > complexity; maintainability > cleverness; fewer dependencies > more.

Hard invariants — never violate without a new ADR in docs/DECISIONS.md:
- AI output is always a DRAFT. Publishing is always a human moderator action.
- The platform must stay fully usable with AI switched off.
- RLS is enabled on every table; the service-role key never reaches the browser.
- Application code never calls an LLM directly — only through the `AIProvider` interface.
- Store references to external content, not copies of copyrighted media.
- Never store submitter IP addresses or fingerprints. AI-detected people default to `redacted`.
- Security and contributor privacy take priority over convenience.

See docs/CONSTITUTION.md and docs/ARCHITECTURE.md before proposing structural changes.
